WEBVTT

00:03.103 --> 00:06.571
<font color="#00ff00">Meredith:</font> <i>Anesthesiology is a lot more
challenging than it looks...</i>

00:06.657 --> 00:08.048
<i>- <font color="#ffff00">[Laughs]</font>
- ..because it's mostly math.</i>

00:08.134 --> 00:10.509
Environment
affects health.

00:10.602 --> 00:12.055
And I want to quantify it.

00:12.149 --> 00:13.891
See if we can have
a positive impact

00:13.977 --> 00:16.414
on patient health
pre- and post-op,

00:16.500 --> 00:18.500
even reduce the need
for heart surgeries.

00:18.687 --> 00:20.476
What kind of environments?

00:20.790 --> 00:22.275
<i><font color="#ff80ff">- ♪ One, two, whatcha gonna do? ♪</font>
- A patient's weight,</i>

00:22.360 --> 00:24.813
<i>their estimated blood volume,
their lung function...</i>

00:24.898 --> 00:27.055
<i>all these variables
have to be accounted for.</i>

00:27.306 --> 00:30.055
Plant life
improves physical well-being.

00:30.141 --> 00:33.328
It decreases anxiety
and lowers blood pressure.

00:33.415 --> 00:35.024
Increases attentiveness.

00:35.110 --> 00:37.594
Parker, leave that tree
by the window.

00:37.680 --> 00:39.500
I want to forget
that we are in the city.

00:39.609 --> 00:40.836
This is a jungle.

00:40.922 --> 00:43.228
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Can you feel that rhythm ♪</font></i>
<i>- It takes careful calculation</i>

00:43.313 --> 00:45.352
<i>to suspend a person
between life and death.</i>

00:46.070 --> 00:48.969
Full-body exposure
to high levels of blue light

00:49.055 --> 00:50.868
reduces systolic blood pressure

00:50.954 --> 00:54.477
the same amount
as it is reduced in certain drug trials.

00:54.632 --> 00:56.226
So this could replace medicine?

00:56.352 --> 00:57.415
I want to find out.

00:57.929 --> 00:59.883
<i>And if one of those variables
is off,</i>

01:00.828 --> 01:02.706
<i>you might wake up
in the middle of your surgery.</i>

01:02.791 --> 01:04.555
So, we all know
the neurological benefits

01:04.641 --> 01:05.688
of puzzles and games.

01:05.774 --> 01:07.422
I want to see
if those same benefits

01:07.508 --> 01:08.625
spread throughout the body,

01:08.726 --> 01:10.671
which brings us
to door number three.

01:10.851 --> 01:12.469
<i>- Or never wake up at all.</i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

01:12.555 --> 01:14.719
I see you've found
the game room, Dr. Bailey.

01:14.853 --> 01:16.376
- <font color="#ffff00">[ <i>Video Game Beeping</i> ]</font>
- How are you feeling?

01:16.461 --> 01:18.883
<font color="#00ff00">Bailey:</font> Oh, my stress levels
have never been better.

01:18.969 --> 01:21.305
Ah, they never give you the long,
skinny piece!

01:21.391 --> 01:22.688
Why do they do that?!

01:22.774 --> 01:25.274
So, any volunteers?

01:25.547 --> 01:26.922
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Do do do do do do do ♪</font></i>

01:27.008 --> 01:28.261
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Good to go ♪</font></i>

01:29.359 --> 01:30.795
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:30.984 --> 01:32.610
Any, uh,
word from your dad?

01:32.696 --> 01:33.946
Have you heard anything
or...

01:34.109 --> 01:35.965
Uh, no.
No, I haven't.

01:36.051 --> 01:37.438
<font color="#ffff00">[Telephone rings in distance]</font>

01:37.524 --> 01:39.594
I have some rounds.
I should probably...

01:39.703 --> 01:40.914
Yeah, sure.

01:41.141 --> 01:42.469
<font color="#ffff00">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

01:42.554 --> 01:44.118
<font color="#ffff00">[Telephone rings in distance]</font>

01:45.477 --> 01:47.274
<font color="#00ff00">Woman on P.A.:</font>
<i>Dr. Martin to Pediatrics.</i>

01:47.453 --> 01:49.312
<i>Dr. Sarah Martin...</i>

01:49.820 --> 01:51.869
Hey, good news... I can make it
to the birthing class today.

01:51.954 --> 01:53.602
I thought you were
covering the ER for me.

01:53.688 --> 01:54.922
You know, so could attend.

01:55.040 --> 01:56.142
Uh, Webber's got it,

01:56.228 --> 01:57.946
but if you'd rather
I didn't go, then...

01:58.032 --> 01:59.854
- No, it's fine. It's great. Uh...
- Okay, great.

01:59.939 --> 02:02.415
Well, I'll do my post-ops,
and then I'll see you up there?

02:04.243 --> 02:05.791
I should have told him
you were coming, too.

02:05.876 --> 02:07.369
Oh, it's fine.
It's better than fine...

02:07.454 --> 02:09.321
it's what I secretly
was hoping for all along.

02:09.407 --> 02:12.009
I think he and I are about
this close to becoming besties.

02:12.095 --> 02:14.243
You're joking,
but it's what I'm rooting for.

02:14.400 --> 02:15.759
Hey, I got to go change into my

02:15.852 --> 02:17.368
"supportive boyfriend" clothes.
You...

02:17.517 --> 02:19.431
- You good?
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> Yes, thank you.

02:19.517 --> 02:20.579
<font color="#ffff00">[Breathes deeply]</font>

02:21.861 --> 02:22.915
Ow!

02:23.381 --> 02:25.251
Ow. <font color="#ffff00">[Groans]</font>

02:25.657 --> 02:28.844
All right, move off
whatever organ you're on, soldier.

02:28.930 --> 02:30.845
<font color="#ffff00">[Exhales Sharply]</font> Okay.

02:31.407 --> 02:33.688
Ah. At ease.

02:34.168 --> 02:35.524
<font color="#ffff00">[Exhales sharply]</font>

02:35.610 --> 02:37.329
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

02:37.415 --> 02:38.758
<font color="#ffff00">[ <i>Line Rings</i> ]</font>

02:38.882 --> 02:40.696
- <font color="#00ff00">Jo:</font> <i>This is Jo. Leave a mess...</i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[CELLPHONE BEEPS]</font>

02:40.782 --> 02:42.438
<font color="#ffff00">[Door opens]</font>

02:42.641 --> 02:45.235
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

02:47.627 --> 02:48.789
What are you doing in here?

02:48.876 --> 02:49.938
Hey. Research.

02:50.024 --> 02:51.649
I needed
a change of scenery,

02:51.735 --> 02:52.946
and, you know,
I have to say,

02:53.032 --> 02:54.844
the plants are actually
very soothing.

02:54.930 --> 02:56.094
What are you working on?

02:58.133 --> 02:59.189
What is it?

02:59.282 --> 03:02.094
Ingestible diagnostic device.

03:02.180 --> 03:03.743
- Ingestible?
- Mm-hmm.

03:03.829 --> 03:05.540
I mean, I think,
I don't know.

03:05.626 --> 03:07.626
It came to me in a dream,
sort of, so...

03:09.274 --> 03:11.657
How's Jo's trip going?
Did she meet her mom?

03:11.743 --> 03:13.543
I don't know.
I haven't talked to her. <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

03:13.680 --> 03:14.876
How's DeLuca?

03:15.266 --> 03:16.922
Where'd you say she was
going, Pittsburgh?

03:17.008 --> 03:18.008
Yeah.

03:18.094 --> 03:20.641
Is he still being weird?
'Cause he's on my service today.

03:20.790 --> 03:22.211
Why do you keep changing
the subject?

03:22.296 --> 03:23.399
Why do you?

03:25.317 --> 03:27.219
She <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>...
She's not answering her phone.

03:27.313 --> 03:28.899
She hasn't texted all day.
I'm worried.

03:29.672 --> 03:32.251
Well, okay, so, she's probably
just gonna come home

03:32.337 --> 03:33.657
and tell you everything.

03:33.743 --> 03:34.811
What about the Italian?

03:34.896 --> 03:36.571
Big blowup with the dad.

03:36.657 --> 03:37.821
Big.

03:38.336 --> 03:40.086
Does not want my input.

03:40.773 --> 03:43.094
- Ohh.
- So I'm just trying to give him a minute.

03:43.251 --> 03:44.947
<font color="#ffff00">[Clears Throat]</font>
Your boyfriend's being weird,

03:45.032 --> 03:46.696
and, uh,
you're hiding out in plants?

03:46.782 --> 03:49.102
Well, if I was hiding out,
you wouldn't be able to find me.

03:49.290 --> 03:51.391
<font color="#ffff00">[ <i>Woman Speaking
Indiistinctly over P.A.</i> ]</font>

03:51.524 --> 03:53.407
<font color="#ffff00">[Door opens, closes]</font>

03:53.493 --> 03:55.594
Blue light lowers
blood pressure?

03:55.680 --> 03:56.883
Significantly.

03:56.969 --> 03:58.977
And some studies
suggest that

03:59.063 --> 04:00.993
it could even
improve your mood, so...

04:01.321 --> 04:03.297
And I'm not saying
it's a cure-all or anything,

04:03.383 --> 04:05.265
but you might want
to spend some time...

04:06.657 --> 04:09.227
Okay, the room doesn't work
that fast...

04:09.883 --> 04:11.102
What's going on?

04:11.297 --> 04:12.321
Nothing.

04:12.465 --> 04:13.774
Nothing?

04:14.360 --> 04:15.977
'Cause the last time
I saw you

04:16.110 --> 04:17.345
there was
a fair amount of crying,

04:17.430 --> 04:19.930
and exactly
zero chair spinning.

04:20.435 --> 04:21.672
Fine.

04:21.942 --> 04:24.258
I might have had
some insanely good sex

04:24.344 --> 04:26.149
at the conference
in San Diego.

04:26.235 --> 04:28.001
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font>
Oh, wait, what?

04:28.087 --> 04:29.141
You had insane sex

04:29.227 --> 04:30.876
with a complete stranger
in San Diego?

04:30.962 --> 04:32.313
Not a complete stranger.

04:32.477 --> 04:34.540
And not insane sex.
Insanely good sex.

04:34.626 --> 04:36.556
And it helped my mood
a lot more than this blue room.

04:36.641 --> 04:39.087
Oh, okay, so,
like a rebound.

04:39.293 --> 04:40.970
- More like muscle bound.
- Oh, oh, oh, oh!

04:41.055 --> 04:42.844
- <font color="#ffff00">[Knock on door]</font>
- Knock, knock.

04:42.930 --> 04:44.657
- Hi.
- Dr. Pierce.

04:44.743 --> 04:45.876
Uh...

04:46.001 --> 04:49.211
I took a look at your
sternal reconstruction thing,

04:49.297 --> 04:50.266
and I e-mailed you some...

04:50.352 --> 04:51.509
- some thoughts.
- Oh, great. Thank you.

04:51.594 --> 04:52.555
Yeah, sorry it took me
so long...

04:52.641 --> 04:54.735
I was at a conference
in San Diego.

04:54.821 --> 04:56.852
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

04:57.158 --> 04:58.407
Uh, oh!

04:58.758 --> 05:01.368
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

05:02.118 --> 05:03.657
- Nice room.
- Yeah.

05:03.743 --> 05:04.946
Very blue.

05:05.165 --> 05:06.269
Yeah.

05:06.743 --> 05:08.938
It's very cool.
Dr. Shepherd.

05:09.141 --> 05:10.573
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

05:10.852 --> 05:11.899
<font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

05:11.985 --> 05:13.875
- Oh, my God.
- It was a one-time thing!

05:13.961 --> 05:15.203
That is it!
I just needed

05:15.289 --> 05:16.860
some pain management.
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

05:17.008 --> 05:18.642
Does this room change colors?
Does it do pink?

05:18.727 --> 05:20.547
- No.
- Okay, then.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.336
<font color="#ffff00">[Door opens]</font>

05:23.219 --> 05:24.391
<font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

05:24.640 --> 05:27.336
So, Mom just decided not to
start back to work this week.

05:27.422 --> 05:29.414
You don't know if she's in pain,
or is she tired?

05:29.500 --> 05:30.587
She didn't give me
any reason.

05:30.672 --> 05:33.141
She waved her hand
and said "cancer card."

05:33.227 --> 05:34.657
That's her
new shorthand for...

05:34.743 --> 05:36.329
- "Stop questioning me."
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> Exactly.

05:36.414 --> 05:37.478
- <font color="#ffff00">[Elevator Bell Rings]</font>
- <font color="#00ff00">Woman:</font> <i>Let's move!</i>

05:37.563 --> 05:38.719
<i>- Go.
- Get the second one.</i>

05:38.805 --> 05:39.931
<font color="#00ff00">Flight Dock:</font> <i>Kari Donnelly, 50,</i>

05:40.016 --> 05:42.142
<i>complains of neck and back pain
after a snowmobile collision.</i>

05:42.227 --> 05:46.039
<i>BP 150 over 90, tachycardic
with some leg weakness on exam.</i>

05:46.125 --> 05:47.133
Okay, got her. Let's go.

05:47.219 --> 05:49.602
Toby Donnelly, 22,
snowmobile passenger.

05:49.688 --> 05:52.047
Sustained a deep soft tissue
injury to the left upper arm.

05:52.133 --> 05:53.173
- Mm-hmm.
- Vital signs stable.

05:53.258 --> 05:54.321
<font color="#00ff00">Man:</font> <i>That's all clear!</i>

05:54.407 --> 05:55.477
Is my mom okay?

05:55.563 --> 05:57.414
She always drives
so fricking fast.

05:57.500 --> 05:59.095
- Will you tell her that? She...
- <font color="#ffff00">[Screams]</font>

05:59.180 --> 06:00.477
All right, let's go!
Let's go! Let's go now!

06:00.562 --> 06:02.821
<i>- <font color="#ffff00">[Speaking Indistinctly]</font>
- On it!</i>

06:03.639 --> 06:05.438
<font color="#00ff00">Woman on P.A.:</font>
<i>Dr. Oper to Oncology.</i>

06:05.524 --> 06:06.474
<i>Dr. Rick Oper...</i>

06:06.560 --> 06:08.276
Hey, I got your page.

06:08.362 --> 06:09.468
Yeah. Well...

06:09.554 --> 06:12.516
11-year-old girl
with chronic pancreatitis. Ouch.

06:12.602 --> 06:14.142
And I've known this kid
since she was 5.

06:14.227 --> 06:16.117
Today, she's getting
a total pancreatectomy.

06:16.203 --> 06:17.789
And you're gonna give her
the good news.

06:17.875 --> 06:19.711
- Why me?
- 'Cause I'm a nice guy.

06:19.861 --> 06:21.701
What... you don't feel
like being a hero today?

06:21.849 --> 06:22.849
<font color="#ffff00">[Elevator bell dings]</font>

06:23.057 --> 06:24.633
<font color="#ffff00">[Telephone rings in distance]</font>

06:25.038 --> 06:27.289
Are you solving for "Y"?
It's 11.

06:27.475 --> 06:29.092
Um... Unh-unh.

06:29.294 --> 06:30.294
It's not.

06:30.531 --> 06:33.672
I took two years of Integral
and Differential Calc.

06:33.758 --> 06:36.125
I was going into theoretical math.
It's 11.

06:36.211 --> 06:39.422
I just do this for fun.
And it's 14.

06:39.969 --> 06:41.165
Shut up!

06:41.398 --> 06:42.922
Sorry. Sorry.

06:43.054 --> 06:45.211
- But how are you <i>that</i> good at math?
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

06:45.389 --> 06:46.929
Qadri, let's do it.

06:47.926 --> 06:49.813
This is Nora Hillridge,
age 11.

06:49.899 --> 06:52.102
She was diagnosed
with hereditary pancreatitis

06:52.188 --> 06:53.188
at age 5.

06:53.343 --> 06:54.845
She's been hospitalized
for the last six months.

06:54.930 --> 06:56.347
And why haven't
we helped her?

06:56.750 --> 06:59.141
A number of criteria
need to align

06:59.227 --> 07:00.577
in order to perform
her surgery...

07:00.696 --> 07:03.383
her APACHE II score
should be below 4,

07:03.625 --> 07:06.852
her amylase, lipase, LDH,
and base deficit

07:06.938 --> 07:08.188
should be within normal limits.

07:08.274 --> 07:10.259
Her fasting glucose and
C peptide levels should be...

07:10.344 --> 07:11.766
All right.
All right, got it.

07:11.852 --> 07:12.902
DeLuca?

07:13.046 --> 07:16.250
The hope has always been
to do a total pancreatectomy

07:16.336 --> 07:17.781
with in islet autotransplantation,

07:17.867 --> 07:21.211
so she won't get diabetes
or even need Insulin shots.

07:21.297 --> 07:24.015
And today,
all the elements have aligned.

07:24.479 --> 07:26.640
Your numbers are perfect,
Nora, and today...

07:26.726 --> 07:28.417
- No.
- ..we are taking you to surgery!

07:28.503 --> 07:30.053
Ahh!

07:30.139 --> 07:32.019
- Nora! <font color="#ffff00">[Laughs]</font>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

07:32.136 --> 07:34.355
Oh, you can go back
to school!

07:34.530 --> 07:35.831
<font color="#ffff00">[Smooches]</font>

07:35.917 --> 07:37.434
<font color="#ffff00">[Laughs]</font>

07:37.576 --> 07:39.126
How long
will I have to recover?

07:39.222 --> 07:40.832
<font color="#00ff00">Dahlia:</font> We'll have you out
of here before you know it.

07:40.917 --> 07:42.667
Thank you, thank you. <font color="#ffff00">[Gasps]</font>

07:42.753 --> 07:45.237
- Thank you! Thank you!
- I...

07:45.474 --> 07:46.657
- <font color="#ffff00">[Laughs]</font>
- Uh, okay.

07:46.742 --> 07:48.459
<font color="#ffff00">[Both laughing]</font>

07:48.560 --> 07:51.344
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

07:53.570 --> 07:55.765
Major Altman?
I didn't see you'd signed up.

07:55.897 --> 07:56.992
Does this room work?

07:57.078 --> 07:59.136
Studies show that 400 nanometers
of blue light...

07:59.221 --> 08:01.375
I just need to know if it works!

08:01.817 --> 08:03.300
I apologize for that.

08:03.495 --> 08:05.708
I started to feel a little sore
about an hour ago,

08:05.794 --> 08:07.078
and <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

08:07.206 --> 08:09.624
I'm hoping that it's just stress,

08:09.710 --> 08:13.703
and if Pierce is onto
something, then I-I just...

08:13.789 --> 08:15.156
<font color="#ffff00">[Screams]</font>

08:15.242 --> 08:17.203
- Okay. Okay, nope.
- Ohh.

08:17.350 --> 08:19.094
Nope, not stress.

08:19.180 --> 08:20.656
Feels more like...

08:20.750 --> 08:23.893
like my body is pushing out
all of my organs.

08:23.979 --> 08:24.789
I'll get a wheelchair.

08:24.875 --> 08:26.771
- Page OB! And Owen Hunt.
- Okay.

08:26.857 --> 08:28.883
Stay right where you are, soldier!

08:29.497 --> 08:30.898
Not you! You go!

08:30.984 --> 08:32.859
Okay, okay, no, no. Okay, no.

08:32.945 --> 08:35.898
Okay, okay, wait, no, no.
<font color="#ffff00">[Screeming Echoes]</font>

08:36.030 --> 08:38.601
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 15 Episode 18</font>

08:38.975 --> 08:42.219
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
Episode Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"Add It Up"</font>

08:45.992 --> 08:48.289
<font color="#ffff00">[indistinct conversations]</font>

08:48.430 --> 08:50.414
<font color="#00ff00">Owen:</font> <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font> Okay.

08:50.570 --> 08:52.617
You think Teddy wants,
uh, soft or firm?

08:52.703 --> 08:54.427
Uh, I think Teddy has
a partner for this class,

08:54.512 --> 08:55.375
so you can head out.

08:55.461 --> 08:57.336
<font color="#00ff00">Sherri:</font> Okay, everyone,
on your mats.

08:57.422 --> 08:59.109
Moms leaning against
partners

08:59.195 --> 09:00.451
- for lumbar support.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

09:00.537 --> 09:01.742
You want to hold
or be held?

09:01.828 --> 09:03.289
- <font color="#ffff00">[Pager Beeps, Vibrates]</font>
- Oh.

09:03.929 --> 09:05.031
Uh, I gotta go.

09:05.117 --> 09:07.008
Y... <font color="#ffff00">[clears throat]</font>

09:07.242 --> 09:10.289
He's very busy and,
uh, important, so...

09:10.484 --> 09:11.650
I'll just...

09:12.211 --> 09:14.656
What is happening down there?
Am I dilated? Effaced?

09:14.742 --> 09:15.664
Is there a foot sticking out?

09:15.750 --> 09:17.344
- I need answers.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

09:17.430 --> 09:18.562
You can scoot up.

09:18.820 --> 09:20.237
- You're not in labor.
- Okay.

09:20.323 --> 09:22.673
Your contractions are sporadic
and not very strong.

09:22.759 --> 09:23.828
Not very strong?

09:23.914 --> 09:25.305
What do they feel like
when they're strong?

09:25.390 --> 09:27.641
You do, however,
have cervical insufficiency.

09:27.796 --> 09:30.570
- Okay, where's the button?
- What button?

09:30.656 --> 09:32.398
I'm putting myself
in Trendelenburg.

09:32.502 --> 09:34.625
Gravity might help
prevent preterm labor.

09:34.711 --> 09:37.047
How about you let me
put you in Trendelenburg?

09:37.133 --> 09:39.282
How about you push some meds
to stop these contractions

09:39.367 --> 09:41.885
and stop pretending like
now isn't the time to panic?

09:41.971 --> 09:43.578
I assure you, Dr. Altman,

09:43.664 --> 09:46.453
I'll do everything I can
to keep the baby inside,

09:46.539 --> 09:47.461
and if she's born today...

09:47.547 --> 09:49.026
No, no, no, no.

09:49.112 --> 09:50.725
She's not ready, and,
frankly, neither am I...

09:50.810 --> 09:53.128
- Wow, this is really not comfortable.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Knock on door]</font>

09:53.214 --> 09:54.453
What the hell happened?

09:54.539 --> 09:56.000
- <font color="#ffff00">[Exhales Sharply]</font>
- Hey.

09:56.676 --> 09:58.179
- <font color="#ffff00">[Breathing Heavily]</font>
- You okay?

09:58.941 --> 10:01.070
<font color="#00ff00">Woman on P.A.:</font> <i>Dr. Campbell
to the Stepdown Unit.</i>

10:01.156 --> 10:02.607
I thought we agreed
we weren't gonna tell people

10:02.692 --> 10:04.312
- about what happened?
- We did.

10:04.398 --> 10:06.375
Why did you tell Maggie
you were in San Diego?

10:06.461 --> 10:07.579
'Cause I was. At a conference.

10:07.664 --> 10:09.749
<font color="#ffff00">[Whispering]</font> Well, I told her
I had sex at a conference.

10:09.834 --> 10:11.540
<font color="#ffff00">[Whispering]</font> Wait, so you
told her about the sex,

10:11.625 --> 10:13.385
but I'm in trouble
for mentioning a location?

10:13.711 --> 10:16.094
Okay, can I just reiterate
that this was a one-time thing?

10:16.180 --> 10:17.230
I mean, it was just...

10:17.380 --> 10:18.359
Pain management, like you said.

10:18.445 --> 10:20.281
For acute pain, not chronic.

10:20.367 --> 10:22.148
One dose. Do not refill.

10:23.002 --> 10:24.742
Ew, sorry. I'm just saying,

10:24.954 --> 10:26.204
to be safe, I think we should probably

10:26.289 --> 10:27.805
steer clear of each other for a while.

10:27.890 --> 10:29.618
- You really think that's necessary?
- I do. Because...

10:29.703 --> 10:30.652
<font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

10:30.738 --> 10:32.656
- ...pheromones.
- What about them?

10:33.250 --> 10:35.054
- I really like yours.
- Okay, then.

10:35.140 --> 10:36.289
I'll avoid you completely.

10:36.375 --> 10:38.292
<font color="#ffff00">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

10:38.378 --> 10:39.758
- You paged?
- You paged?

10:40.136 --> 10:43.234
Oh, Dr. Shepherd, uh, Dr. Lincoln,

10:43.320 --> 10:45.609
Kari Donnelly...
she rolled her snowmobile.

10:45.695 --> 10:47.047
<font color="#00ff00">Kari: </font>Not on purpose.

10:47.133 --> 10:48.476
Now, the films just came up,

10:48.562 --> 10:50.523
but I need to help Dr. Avery.

10:51.909 --> 10:53.883
Toby says I was driving too fast.

10:53.969 --> 10:55.452
I tell them,

10:55.678 --> 10:57.395
why have a throttle
if you don't crank it?

10:57.481 --> 10:58.656
Well, this may be why.

10:58.756 --> 11:01.000
Film shows fractures at C4 and 5.

11:01.124 --> 11:03.922
Is that bad? How bad is it?

11:04.008 --> 11:06.765
We won't know how bad it is
until we get some scans.

11:06.851 --> 11:08.398
- Can you feel this?
- Yes.

11:08.484 --> 11:09.733
That's good.

11:09.830 --> 11:11.742
- I'd like to take her for an MRI.
- I'd like to get her an MRI.

11:11.827 --> 11:13.375
<font color="#ffff00">[Telephone ringing in distance]</font>

11:13.461 --> 11:14.595
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

11:14.681 --> 11:15.931
Oh, God.

11:16.398 --> 11:17.522
<font color="#ffff00">[Siren wails in distance]</font>

11:17.607 --> 11:19.500
Hey, uh, how we doing here?

11:19.681 --> 11:21.539
No palpable pulse in the arm,

11:21.625 --> 11:23.695
getting a weak Doppler signal,
it sounds like.

11:23.781 --> 11:25.731
Got some arterial compromise, as well.

11:25.845 --> 11:27.453
I-Is my mom okay?

11:27.640 --> 11:29.859
Oh, she's stable... we'll...
we'll know more soon, okay?

11:30.070 --> 11:32.242
Let's make sure you have
no other injuries.

11:32.969 --> 11:34.781
Snowmobiling was her idea.

11:35.039 --> 11:37.476
She's always pushing me
to face my fears.

11:37.562 --> 11:40.703
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> She was right.
It was a lot of fun.

11:41.502 --> 11:42.918
God, why is she always right?

11:43.004 --> 11:44.148
I know how you feel.

11:44.234 --> 11:47.052
I mean, fun till
she swerved to miss a tree

11:47.138 --> 11:49.531
and flipped us five times.

11:50.351 --> 11:52.773
- Hey, uh, we should get a CT angio...
- <font color="#ffff00">[BREATHES SHARPLY]</font>

11:52.859 --> 11:55.304
...to determine the location
of her vascular injuries.

11:55.434 --> 11:57.187
- "Their."
- Excuse me?

11:57.273 --> 11:59.234
"Their" injury, not <i>"her."</i>

11:59.320 --> 12:00.770
I'm a <i>"they."</i>

12:00.953 --> 12:02.601
I'm gender-queer.

12:03.053 --> 12:04.937
- Non-binary.
- Got it.

12:05.038 --> 12:06.988
Thank you for letting us know
your pronouns.

12:07.213 --> 12:09.531
Their preferred pronouns
are "they" and "them."

12:09.617 --> 12:12.890
Oh, okay, uh, yes.
Uh, w-well, a-all right, then.

12:12.976 --> 12:17.250
Um, w-well, let's get you... all?

12:17.406 --> 12:18.976
"You" is fine.

12:19.062 --> 12:21.656
Great.
Well, your ultrasound is fine.

12:21.742 --> 12:23.195
Let's get you up to CT.

12:23.685 --> 12:26.140
<font color="#ffff00">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

12:28.693 --> 12:30.031
This is really
why you paged me?

12:30.117 --> 12:31.117
Just read.

12:32.033 --> 12:34.234
"Glenda mapped a town
using a scale

12:34.320 --> 12:36.437
that was 5 inches
and equals 1 yard.

12:36.805 --> 12:38.622
What scale factor does her drawing use?"

12:38.723 --> 12:39.790
Okay, one yard equals three,

12:39.875 --> 12:42.336
divided by seven and 1/5...

12:42.422 --> 12:45.250
5 to 7.2 is the ratio.

12:46.033 --> 12:47.797
You didn't write!
You need to write.

12:47.883 --> 12:49.403
- Let's go again.
- <font color="#00ff00">DeLuca:</font> Okay, okay.

12:49.565 --> 12:50.828
Let's get her prepped, guys.

12:50.914 --> 12:52.981
One more, please?
An easy one.

12:53.560 --> 12:54.851
All right.

12:55.137 --> 12:58.055
Okay. "A line L is perpendicular

12:58.141 --> 13:01.492
to the line 2x - 5y - 8 = 0.

13:01.578 --> 13:03.625
What is the slope of the line L?"

13:03.715 --> 13:05.498
That was supposed to be an <i>easy</i> one?

13:05.584 --> 13:07.285
Hey, Nora. <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

13:08.523 --> 13:10.289
I, uh... I got some bad news.

13:10.399 --> 13:11.937
I just ran your pre-op blood work,

13:12.023 --> 13:13.023
and I don't know why,

13:13.109 --> 13:14.703
but your glucose level has shot way up.

13:14.984 --> 13:17.312
No! She was just in the clear!

13:17.726 --> 13:20.039
Was it a lab error this morning,
or what happened?

13:20.125 --> 13:21.133
I'm not sure yet.

13:21.219 --> 13:23.304
The bottom line is, we have to
put you on an Insulin drip

13:23.389 --> 13:24.640
to lower your blood sugar,

13:24.882 --> 13:26.600
which means we have to
postpone your surgery

13:26.685 --> 13:27.766
till we can sort this out.

13:27.975 --> 13:30.228
It's been six months
getting her to this point.

13:30.384 --> 13:32.901
Well, let's just keep
our fingers crossed, okay?

13:33.102 --> 13:36.664
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

13:39.080 --> 13:40.864
Negative five over two.

13:41.316 --> 13:42.414
Beat you.

13:42.500 --> 13:43.767
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

13:45.712 --> 13:48.054
I don't know how this happened.
Sorry about this.

13:48.375 --> 13:50.344
Don't be sorry for me.
Be sorry for her.

13:52.060 --> 13:53.773
Did Meredith ask you to do this?

13:53.970 --> 13:55.078
Throw me a bone? Give me a win?

13:55.163 --> 13:56.851
Is that what this is?
'Cause I'm good.

13:56.937 --> 13:58.648
I had a bad week, and I moved on.

13:58.734 --> 14:00.035
I don't need any favors.

14:01.517 --> 14:02.765
<font color="#ffff00">[Scoffs]</font>

14:02.851 --> 14:03.992
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

14:04.297 --> 14:06.174
<font color="#ffff00">[Computer beeping]</font>

14:09.222 --> 14:11.258
I've got to get off this case.
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

14:12.412 --> 14:13.508
<font color="#ffff00">[Computer beeps]</font>

14:13.609 --> 14:14.719
Scans are up.

14:15.531 --> 14:16.481
<font color="#ffff00">[Keys clack]</font>

14:16.567 --> 14:17.616
<font color="#ffff00">[Beeping]</font>

14:17.702 --> 14:20.518
- Bulging disc at C5.
- Crap.

14:20.611 --> 14:22.070
Did you see L-3?

14:22.156 --> 14:23.706
Yeah, L-4 is worse.

14:23.792 --> 14:26.343
Total obliteration of the CSF space

14:26.451 --> 14:27.605
and displacement of the cauda.

14:27.690 --> 14:30.094
She could end up paraplegic.

14:30.761 --> 14:33.125
I'd rather not handle
this case on my own.

14:33.360 --> 14:35.219
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

14:35.443 --> 14:36.781
Understood.

14:37.173 --> 14:40.672
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

14:42.178 --> 14:44.914
<font color="#ffff00">[ <i>Video Game Beeping</i> ]</font>

14:45.003 --> 14:46.521
If you're gonna take up
all my time slots,

14:46.606 --> 14:48.696
could you at least put a cuff on
so I can take your data?

14:48.781 --> 14:50.149
I'm about to beat
the high score.

14:50.235 --> 14:52.047
Which you just set
20 minutes ago.

14:52.155 --> 14:53.696
Oh, then you should've
hooked me up then.

14:53.781 --> 14:55.821
You pressed "restart" before
we could get the cuff on you.

14:55.906 --> 14:56.989
You snooze, you...

14:57.075 --> 14:58.892
Oh, oh, ah!

14:59.048 --> 15:01.699
See?! Look what happened!

15:01.964 --> 15:03.320
- <font color="#ffff00">[Knock on door]</font>
- Ah!

15:03.422 --> 15:05.687
I was wondering if we could
borrow Dr. Schmitt.

15:05.927 --> 15:07.544
- Is it urgent?
- Yes.

15:07.779 --> 15:09.812
No. No.

15:10.516 --> 15:11.805
I have a patient
who's a math whiz,

15:11.890 --> 15:13.490
and she's crushing me,
and I need backup.

15:13.709 --> 15:16.383
May I go? In school,
they called me "Numbers."

15:16.633 --> 15:18.953
- But not kindly.
- Yeah, go.

15:19.367 --> 15:20.383
Hold on.

15:20.469 --> 15:23.875
Uh, just how good is
this math whiz?

15:24.353 --> 15:26.765
Yeah, please define "whiz"?

15:27.375 --> 15:29.106
<font color="#ffff00">[Rival sons' "do your worst" plays]</font>

15:29.344 --> 15:31.812
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

15:34.429 --> 15:37.359
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Oh, my, oh, my baby ♪</font></i>

15:37.471 --> 15:40.469
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Devil's gonna get you
if I don't first ♪</font></i>

15:40.603 --> 15:43.375
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Take my, take my body ♪</font></i>

15:43.461 --> 15:46.492
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Take my body and do your worst ♪</font></i>

15:46.679 --> 15:48.070
<font color="#ffff00">[Thump echoes]</font>

15:48.344 --> 15:52.447
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

15:56.578 --> 15:58.640
"Insufficient cervix." I mean...

15:58.726 --> 16:02.791
"insufficient" is something
I've never been called

16:02.877 --> 16:03.760
in my entire life.

16:03.845 --> 16:05.929
Are you sure this is
really the best option?

16:06.015 --> 16:08.797
Dr. Altman is following
her own course of treatment.

16:08.883 --> 16:10.800
That being said, um,
I agree with it.

16:10.885 --> 16:13.062
There is no hourglassing
of the membranes anymore,

16:13.148 --> 16:14.828
so I think it's working.

16:15.056 --> 16:16.572
- Um, I'll check on you every hour.
- Okay.

16:16.657 --> 16:18.477
Okay, is there anything
I can do to help, or...

16:18.562 --> 16:21.812
Stay calm and talk to the baby.
Reassure her.

16:21.953 --> 16:23.750
It'll be good for her
to hear your voices.

16:23.843 --> 16:26.398
- Okay. Thank you.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Breathes Deeply]</font>

16:26.484 --> 16:29.051
- <font color="#ffff00">[Inhales deeply]</font>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door opens, closes]</font>

16:29.137 --> 16:30.336
<font color="#ffff00">[Clears throat]</font>

16:34.218 --> 16:36.015
<font color="#ffff00">[Baby-Talk]</font> Hey there, little one.

16:36.366 --> 16:38.804
We still haven't bought you a crib,

16:38.890 --> 16:40.734
but we're almost ready.

16:40.820 --> 16:41.859
- Owen.
- Eh...

16:41.945 --> 16:42.865
My face is up here.

16:42.950 --> 16:43.943
<font color="#ffff00">[Normal Voice]</font> I'm not talking to you.

16:44.028 --> 16:45.301
<font color="#ffff00">[Inhales deeply, clears throat]</font>

16:45.386 --> 16:47.601
<font color="#ffff00">[Baby-Talk]</font> And you wait till you meet

16:47.687 --> 16:49.172
your big brother, Leo.

16:49.257 --> 16:51.258
He's got so many toys
to share with you.

16:51.344 --> 16:52.695
Uh, okay, you can't use that voice.

16:52.780 --> 16:53.866
<font color="#ffff00">[Normal Voice?]</font>

16:54.359 --> 16:55.778
<font color="#ffff00">[Inhales deeply]</font>

16:55.864 --> 16:57.320
<font color="#ffff00">[Deep Voice]</font> This is your dad.

16:57.564 --> 16:58.547
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

16:58.633 --> 17:00.610
- I'm very pleased to meet you.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> Okay.

17:00.695 --> 17:01.961
- Okay? Okay?
- That's perfect.

17:02.047 --> 17:03.518
Now she'll be afraid to come out.

17:03.604 --> 17:06.390
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> Pleeeasse stay inside

17:06.476 --> 17:08.242
for another month or two, okay?

17:08.328 --> 17:10.078
- Okay.
- Okay, you're freaking me out now.

17:10.164 --> 17:11.686
<font color="#ffff00">[Both laugh]</font>

17:11.872 --> 17:14.875
1,000 plus 20 plus 30 plus 1,000

17:15.015 --> 17:17.633
plus 1,030 plus 1,000 plus 20 equals...

17:17.719 --> 17:18.617
<font color="#ffff00">[All]</font> 5,000!

17:18.703 --> 17:20.036
- 4,100!
- 4,100!

17:20.121 --> 17:21.741
What? I call witchcraft!

17:21.826 --> 17:23.851
I got it right!
But she got there first.

17:23.936 --> 17:25.173
I bet you let me win.

17:25.259 --> 17:27.042
Little girl,
ask any of these people

17:27.127 --> 17:29.187
if I ever <i>let anybody win anything.</i>

17:29.304 --> 17:30.346
She hasn't ever.

17:30.431 --> 17:31.656
<font color="#ffff00">[Laughter]</font>

17:31.742 --> 17:33.508
I give up. This is embarrassing.

17:33.664 --> 17:35.578
Don't give up, be on my team.

17:35.664 --> 17:36.906
I don't think I make the cut.

17:36.992 --> 17:38.492
Come on. Come on.

17:38.648 --> 17:39.856
- There you go.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

17:39.941 --> 17:40.957
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

17:41.042 --> 17:42.617
This is so nice of you.

17:43.562 --> 17:44.827
<font color="#ffff00">[Exhales Deeply]</font> True or false...

17:44.912 --> 17:46.851
0.9 repeating equals one?

17:47.416 --> 17:50.835
<font color="#00ff00">Bailey:</font> Okay, wait, I-i-if
3.9 repeating is four...

17:50.952 --> 17:53.062
<font color="#00ff00">Maggie:</font> Times... Times 10...
- <font color="#00ff00">Levi:</font> False!

17:53.148 --> 17:54.328
No, no, true!

17:54.414 --> 17:55.992
No, wait, I-It's infinite 9s!

17:56.086 --> 17:57.306
- Oh, Schmitt, shush!
- True.

17:57.391 --> 17:58.541
It's true. Here.

17:58.626 --> 18:01.336
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

18:01.684 --> 18:03.802
- Well, if you do it like that.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Nora LAUGHS]</font>

18:03.965 --> 18:05.648
<font color="#ffff00">[Computer beeping]</font>

18:05.733 --> 18:06.883
<font color="#ffff00">[Machinery whirring]</font>

18:06.968 --> 18:08.985
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font> Nothing's going on, right?

18:09.117 --> 18:10.567
With my mom?

18:11.531 --> 18:12.727
Nothing I should be worried about?

18:12.812 --> 18:16.025
It's not, like, s-something,
and you're just not telling me?

18:16.406 --> 18:17.914
Now, why would you say that?

18:18.633 --> 18:21.230
Oh, I don't know...
because I blithely assumed

18:21.315 --> 18:23.562
my mother did not have cancer
when, in fact, she did,

18:23.648 --> 18:24.828
and none of you told me.

18:25.086 --> 18:29.304
Well, I found out after you,
if you'll recall.

18:30.636 --> 18:32.797
- Look, I know you're scared, son.
- I'm not scared,

18:33.211 --> 18:36.562
all right? I'm just...
concerned.

18:37.661 --> 18:39.164
They're all settled.

18:39.276 --> 18:40.776
<font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

18:42.225 --> 18:45.437
Do we really have
to use this plural thing,

18:45.562 --> 18:46.594
even when she can't hear us?

18:46.679 --> 18:48.515
While <i>they</i>... they can't hear us.

18:48.609 --> 18:50.693
Okay, yeah.
It's not that complicated.

18:50.778 --> 18:51.961
Not that complicated?

18:52.046 --> 18:53.609
We're talking about
a single entity,

18:53.695 --> 18:54.758
but "they" is plural.

18:54.844 --> 18:57.600
I mean, it requires a plural verb.

18:57.898 --> 19:00.031
Or am I supposed to say, "They is"?

19:00.117 --> 19:02.414
No, look,
if you're in a movie theater

19:02.539 --> 19:04.593
and somebody's coat is left in a seat,

19:04.679 --> 19:05.523
and you bring it to the Usher,

19:05.609 --> 19:06.953
what do you say to the Usher?

19:07.039 --> 19:08.411
Well, a number of things.

19:08.496 --> 19:11.992
Um, I might say,
"Someone left behind a coat,"

19:12.172 --> 19:13.422
or, "I found someone's coat,"

19:13.508 --> 19:15.320
or, "Turn this in to the lost and found."

19:15.406 --> 19:17.220
I might say,
"Somebody left their coat."

19:17.305 --> 19:19.055
Then you'd be grammatically
incorrect.

19:19.140 --> 19:20.507
Ungrammatical.

19:21.500 --> 19:23.484
Excuse me?

19:23.570 --> 19:27.140
Uh, something's either
grammatical or it's not.

19:27.234 --> 19:28.598
"Grammatically incorrect" is like saying

19:28.683 --> 19:31.067
something is right-wrong.

19:31.152 --> 19:32.859
<font color="#ffff00">[Computer beeps]</font>

19:33.026 --> 19:34.904
- Scans are up.
- It's about time.

19:34.989 --> 19:37.773
All right, Helm,
what do you see?

19:38.250 --> 19:40.810
Absence of flow in
the mid-brachial artery.

19:40.992 --> 19:42.745
Okay, we need to get her up
to the OR.

19:42.830 --> 19:44.164
Really?

19:46.100 --> 19:48.117
Okay, them, them, them!

19:48.586 --> 19:49.914
Can we go now?

19:50.338 --> 19:51.921
Almighty...

19:52.328 --> 19:54.857
Now I feel pins and needles.

19:55.250 --> 19:56.673
You still feeling this?

19:56.766 --> 19:58.031
I do...

19:58.713 --> 20:00.147
but less.

20:01.248 --> 20:03.508
Why am I...
Why am I feeling it less?

20:03.594 --> 20:06.523
Kari, you suffered two injuries
to your spine.

20:06.703 --> 20:08.604
The lower one is quite severe.

20:08.906 --> 20:11.218
Your neuro exam is getting
progressively worse,

20:11.304 --> 20:12.484
so we need to get in there

20:12.570 --> 20:15.144
before you are paralyzed
from the waist down.

20:15.508 --> 20:17.046
<font color="#ffff00">[Voice Breaking]</font>
I might become paralyzed?

20:17.131 --> 20:19.062
- No...
- We're gonna do everything we can

20:19.148 --> 20:21.017
to reverse
the compression of the nerves.

20:21.102 --> 20:23.656
<font color="#ffff00">[Crying]</font> Oh, God, please...

20:23.742 --> 20:25.304
<font color="#ffff00">[Crying]</font>

20:27.054 --> 20:29.250
I can't do a wheelchair.

20:29.719 --> 20:31.693
I never sit!

20:31.779 --> 20:33.848
<font color="#ffff00">[Crying]</font>

20:34.000 --> 20:35.867
Go... Go ask Toby.

20:36.030 --> 20:40.320
W-We're supposed to do
a sprint triathlon next month.

20:40.469 --> 20:43.047
We are going to do
everything that we can.

20:43.133 --> 20:44.249
<font color="#ffff00">[Crying]</font>

20:44.706 --> 20:46.289
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

20:46.633 --> 20:48.077
Your boyfriend's being a jerk.

20:48.162 --> 20:49.545
- What did he do?
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door Slams]</font>

20:49.630 --> 20:51.562
- <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>
- Oh, wait. None of my business.

20:51.883 --> 20:54.515
Uh, he has to work
this all out by himself.

20:54.601 --> 20:55.821
I was just trying to do him
a favor.

20:55.906 --> 20:57.711
Well, I'm not getting involved,

20:57.797 --> 21:00.001
and please don't bring
any stress into the green zone.

21:00.087 --> 21:01.562
<font color="#ffff00">[Knock on door]</font>

21:02.076 --> 21:04.156
- Hey. There you are.
- Hey.

21:04.242 --> 21:06.343
I was just gonna
actually take a break.

21:06.429 --> 21:07.446
You want to go grab a coffee?

21:07.531 --> 21:09.383
Uh, I meant Dr. Karev.

21:09.469 --> 21:10.554
Oh.

21:10.640 --> 21:12.667
Um, we think we know
why Nora's glucose shot up.

21:12.760 --> 21:15.523
Qadri found this under her pillow.

21:15.875 --> 21:18.226
We think she may have sabotaged
the surgery.

21:19.069 --> 21:20.542
We got to go.

21:20.781 --> 21:21.844
Yep.

21:21.930 --> 21:25.531
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

21:30.787 --> 21:33.975
Why would you do this when
we've been waiting and waiting?

21:34.061 --> 21:35.193
- Why?
- Mom, stop.

21:35.279 --> 21:37.834
I'm not stopping
until you tell us why you...

21:37.920 --> 21:39.601
Because I don't want
to go back to school!

21:39.687 --> 21:41.254
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

21:43.795 --> 21:45.279
I hate it.

21:45.724 --> 21:48.912
It's all cliques and stupid
girls with stupid crushes

21:48.998 --> 21:51.983
and stupid boys who get mad
when I beat them at math.

21:52.092 --> 21:53.850
Nobody sits with me at lunch.

21:53.936 --> 21:55.655
- What about Lauren?
- I missed too much school

21:55.740 --> 21:56.866
because I'm sick all the time,

21:56.951 --> 21:58.990
so she found other kids to sit with.

22:01.121 --> 22:03.436
I don't have any friends there.

22:05.545 --> 22:07.245
But here I do.

22:08.064 --> 22:09.662
So I want to stay here.

22:11.184 --> 22:12.670
Nora, we'll be checking your labs

22:12.756 --> 22:14.116
once you finish your Insulin drip.

22:14.581 --> 22:15.786
Once your labs stabilize...

22:15.872 --> 22:17.140
I'll just drink more juice.

22:17.871 --> 22:19.466
I don't want the surgery.

22:20.693 --> 22:23.100
It's my body. I don't want it.

22:24.951 --> 22:27.600
I taught her that.
That it's her body.

22:27.725 --> 22:29.965
I'm not sure what to do here.

22:30.467 --> 22:31.873
Eileen, can we talk?

22:32.006 --> 22:34.514
<font color="#00ff00">Woman on P.A.:</font>
<i>Inpatient Services, 3343.</i>

22:34.733 --> 22:37.475
<i>Inpatient Services, 3343.</i>

22:37.615 --> 22:38.826
I didn't know...

22:38.912 --> 22:40.740
I didn't know
she hated school.

22:40.826 --> 22:42.812
I didn't know she and Lauren
weren't friends anymore.

22:42.897 --> 22:44.201
How did I not know?

22:44.287 --> 22:46.320
Well, they reach an age
where they like to keep secrets,

22:46.405 --> 22:48.398
like to figure things out for themselves.
It's not on you.

22:48.483 --> 22:50.146
I called Lauren a bitch once.

22:50.271 --> 22:53.467
Not to her face, but behind
her back, to my daughter,

22:53.553 --> 22:55.233
I called her 10-year-old
best friend a bitch

22:55.318 --> 22:57.576
because she was being a bitch. To my kid.

22:57.662 --> 23:01.037
And I wanted to protect her
and be on her side,

23:01.123 --> 23:04.076
but maybe that's why Nora
doesn't talk to me anymore.

23:04.459 --> 23:07.295
Maybe I wasn't supposed
to react, just listen.

23:07.381 --> 23:09.857
But I'm not super great at that
historically, so...

23:10.029 --> 23:11.631
I'm not sure
what I'm supposed to do now.

23:11.717 --> 23:13.163
You're supposed
to make her get the surgery.

23:13.248 --> 23:15.092
- Today. Right now.
- DeLuca...

23:15.178 --> 23:16.483
Every kid gets bullied at school.

23:16.568 --> 23:18.951
Most kids hate school at some
point or another, right?

23:19.037 --> 23:20.670
Are you saying
I should hold her down...

23:20.756 --> 23:21.920
- Yes.
- No, no, look,

23:22.006 --> 23:23.185
this is my patient, DeLuca...

23:23.271 --> 23:24.482
I don't know Nora.

23:24.568 --> 23:26.624
I'm not attached to whether she
has friends at school or not,

23:26.709 --> 23:29.037
but I would like to see her not die.

23:29.123 --> 23:30.615
She's not dying.

23:30.701 --> 23:31.935
Oh, my God, what are you...

23:32.021 --> 23:33.862
- DeLuca.
- Look, she's in pain, right?

23:34.107 --> 23:36.162
Every time her pancreas flares up,

23:36.248 --> 23:38.092
it's extremely painful for her.

23:38.178 --> 23:39.593
She's getting this surgery for a reason,

23:39.678 --> 23:40.803
so just make her get it.

23:40.889 --> 23:42.093
Make her get the help that she needs.

23:42.178 --> 23:43.339
Look, you are dismissed, Dr. DeLuca.

23:43.424 --> 23:45.006
Walk away now.

23:45.389 --> 23:47.396
Walk away now, or you're fired.

23:47.631 --> 23:50.373
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

23:52.900 --> 23:54.567
<font color="#ffff00">[Breathes deeply]</font>

23:56.529 --> 23:58.060
- I can't do this.
- Come on.

23:58.146 --> 23:59.498
I can't. It's just... It's weird.

23:59.584 --> 24:00.843
I don't know how to explain it.
I mean, I can...

24:00.928 --> 24:03.779
I can give her orders like...
like... like she's a soldier.

24:03.865 --> 24:04.787
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> Are you serious?

24:04.873 --> 24:08.599
What? I'm good at that.
Th-This baby-talk thing...

24:08.685 --> 24:10.373
it <font color="#ffff00">[Groans]</font>... it just...
I don't know.

24:10.459 --> 24:11.639
It's not my thing.
It makes me feel...

24:11.724 --> 24:14.136
I don't know... shy.

24:14.326 --> 24:15.904
Oh, I-I'll turn around.

24:15.990 --> 24:18.073
- How about that?
- <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

24:18.158 --> 24:20.927
<font color="#ffff00">[Exhales Sharply]</font> Okay.

24:22.096 --> 24:23.312
Hello.

24:23.637 --> 24:24.875
Hi!

24:25.177 --> 24:27.114
<i>Guten Tag. That's German.</i>

24:27.200 --> 24:29.001
Technically, it means "good day," but...

24:30.552 --> 24:31.820
I'm your mom.

24:32.419 --> 24:33.568
But you probably
already know that

24:33.653 --> 24:34.551
'cause you're floating
around inside me.

24:34.637 --> 24:36.420
- I'm terrible at this. I can't... I...
- You're doing great.

24:36.505 --> 24:38.114
No, I'm not. I'm... I'm terrible at it,

24:38.200 --> 24:39.427
and I'm already failing as a mom.

24:39.512 --> 24:41.059
I'm... I'm insufficient.

24:41.145 --> 24:42.271
Teddy, that doesn't even make sense.

24:42.356 --> 24:44.333
Look, and I'm sure
I caused whatever it was

24:44.419 --> 24:45.506
that made her want
to come out early.

24:45.591 --> 24:48.278
I mean, I'm on my feet too long
and didn't drink enough water,

24:48.364 --> 24:50.294
or probably forgot to take
a prenatal one day.

24:50.380 --> 24:52.497
You know, now she's gonna
be born prematurely

24:52.583 --> 24:54.380
with underdeveloped lungs and...

24:54.466 --> 24:57.051
and low birth weight and no crib

24:57.137 --> 24:58.466
and a... a terrified mom,

24:58.552 --> 25:00.350
- who, despite being a surgeon...
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

25:00.435 --> 25:03.200
...knows crap about...
about taking care of babies...

25:03.286 --> 25:04.569
What are you doing?

25:04.655 --> 25:06.004
- I...<font color="#ffff00">[grunts]</font>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Metal thuds]</font>

25:06.407 --> 25:08.567
...am trying to show you
that you are not alone.

25:08.653 --> 25:10.570
Or, at least I think I am.

25:10.656 --> 25:12.907
- Hold on. <font color="#ffff00">[Grunts]</font>
- Owen. Oh.

25:13.030 --> 25:14.621
<font color="#ffff00">[Grunting]</font>

25:14.755 --> 25:16.239
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> Owen,
you don't have to do this.

25:16.324 --> 25:18.114
Give me a minute.
<font color="#ffff00">[GRUNTING]</font>

25:18.371 --> 25:20.074
- Whew!
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

25:20.160 --> 25:23.245
Whew! Oh, yeah.

25:24.498 --> 25:26.848
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Hands clasp]</font>

25:27.620 --> 25:31.042
<font color="#00ff00">Jackson:</font> All right, Helm,
what are some other ways

25:31.128 --> 25:33.855
that we could've
prepared this vessel?

25:33.941 --> 25:37.691
<font color="#00ff00">Taryn:</font> We could've done a vein patch
or a saphenous vein graft.

25:37.777 --> 25:39.316
Her anasto...

25:39.495 --> 25:42.066
<i>T-Their</i> anastomosis looks good.

25:42.183 --> 25:44.144
Hm, see? That wasn't so hard, was it?

25:44.230 --> 25:46.706
Well, yes, it was,
as a matter of fact.

25:46.933 --> 25:49.331
It was wholly unnatural
to my ear.

25:49.785 --> 25:54.285
You know, I had a mechanic
who called me Ricky

25:54.488 --> 25:57.120
no matter how many times
I corrected him.

25:57.206 --> 25:58.824
Best mechanic I ever had.

25:59.144 --> 26:00.144
I fired him.

26:00.230 --> 26:02.386
You fired a guy 'cause
he called you Ricky?

26:02.472 --> 26:03.863
I'm not a Ricky.

26:04.011 --> 26:05.902
That's kind of a false equivalent.

26:06.050 --> 26:08.527
Comparing an annoying nickname
to misgendering...

26:08.613 --> 26:11.245
I'm just saying that
I understand what it's like

26:11.331 --> 26:13.144
when you're called
something you aren't.

26:13.488 --> 26:15.832
I've been called
a lot worse than Ricky.

26:16.199 --> 26:18.886
It's just... just that
the world moves fast,

26:18.972 --> 26:21.503
and I'm... I'm trying to keep up,

26:21.589 --> 26:22.566
and I'm trying to adjust,

26:22.652 --> 26:25.104
and your attitude is not
helping the process.

26:25.190 --> 26:26.199
<font color="#ffff00">[Liquid suctioning]</font>

26:26.285 --> 26:29.131
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font> I had a girlfriend
call me Jackie once.

26:29.374 --> 26:30.866
Did you break up with her?

26:30.951 --> 26:33.640
- Damn straight I did.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

26:33.929 --> 26:36.738
Dr. Karev, Nora's new
glucose panel came back.

26:36.823 --> 26:38.421
Ah, this is good.

26:38.507 --> 26:41.062
This is good. And her
potassium level is down, too.

26:41.286 --> 26:42.546
So we can do it?

26:42.632 --> 26:44.952
I think we can
if we can talk her into it.

26:45.124 --> 26:46.548
<font color="#00ff00">Woman on P.A.: </font> <i>Dr. Fisher,
call Cardio-Path Lab.</i>

26:46.633 --> 26:47.653
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

26:47.738 --> 26:49.084
<i>Dr. Fisher, call Cardio-Path Lab.</i>

26:49.169 --> 26:50.281
Damn it.

26:50.448 --> 26:53.188
You try to help a guy out a little,
and now I gotta fire him.

26:53.273 --> 26:55.077
<font color="#ffff00">[Telephone rings in distance]</font>

26:55.336 --> 26:57.158
Yeah, you know,
I was about your age

26:57.244 --> 26:59.928
when I moved with my mom
from Italy to Wisconsin.

27:00.013 --> 27:01.827
And <font color="#ffff00">[Exhales Sharply]</font>
they hated me.

27:01.919 --> 27:03.398
I could barely speak any English.

27:03.484 --> 27:06.235
They called me "DeLoser"
for two years straight.

27:06.687 --> 27:08.663
It was tough, but I got through it.

27:08.922 --> 27:11.984
And trust me...
you are way cooler than I was.

27:12.070 --> 27:13.288
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>
Unhunh.

27:13.448 --> 27:15.599
And my hair... you gotta
see my hair, Nora.

27:15.685 --> 27:16.781
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

27:16.867 --> 27:18.731
- Look at this.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Cellphone Key Clicking]</font>

27:19.825 --> 27:21.671
Hm? <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

27:21.757 --> 27:22.940
Huh?

27:23.026 --> 27:24.296
That's me.

27:24.514 --> 27:26.843
Believe me...
that kid got bullied.

27:26.929 --> 27:28.301
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

27:28.628 --> 27:31.513
Nora, kids are mean, and
they're always gonna be mean.

27:32.062 --> 27:34.367
But you can kick all their asses
at math.

27:34.453 --> 27:36.288
That makes you
better than them.

27:36.835 --> 27:38.304
You're gonna find friends.

27:38.390 --> 27:39.974
You already made a bunch here,
right?

27:40.420 --> 27:42.671
I'm gonna let you in
on a little secret, too.

27:43.273 --> 27:45.073
<font color="#ffff00">[Whispering]</font> We're all
a bunch of nerds here.

27:45.158 --> 27:47.108
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> And we like you a lot.

27:47.193 --> 27:48.376
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

27:48.461 --> 27:49.978
And you're gonna find
more of us...

27:50.148 --> 27:51.406
I promise you.

27:52.242 --> 27:54.085
You just got
to push through.

27:55.114 --> 27:56.718
So can you trust me?

27:57.390 --> 27:58.787
And push through?

27:59.109 --> 28:00.687
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

28:00.949 --> 28:02.828
Yeah? All right.

28:02.914 --> 28:03.935
<font color="#ffff00">[Beeping continues]</font>

28:04.065 --> 28:05.281
This jacket's hilarious.

28:05.392 --> 28:07.016
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> Hey, I still have that jacket.

28:07.101 --> 28:08.463
<font color="#ffff00">[Both chuckle]</font>

28:08.710 --> 28:11.507
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

28:18.656 --> 28:20.085
<font color="#00ff00">Amelia:</font> Pick-ups, please.

28:20.683 --> 28:23.546
<font color="#00ff00">Link:</font> You did a beautiful job
on that first laminectomy.

28:23.843 --> 28:27.031
Well, this one's tougher.
The vertebra is crushed.

28:27.223 --> 28:29.164
This is the one that...
Let me see if I can ease if off.

28:29.249 --> 28:31.249
Careful.
If it shifts even a little,

28:31.327 --> 28:32.710
she's in a wheelchair forever.

28:32.881 --> 28:34.778
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font> Thanks for that.

28:34.864 --> 28:37.179
- No pressure.
- Well, it's what it is.

28:37.282 --> 28:39.359
And she's got that triathlon
with her kid.

28:39.896 --> 28:40.916
Good.

28:41.140 --> 28:43.734
Good. Good.

28:44.413 --> 28:45.532
Okay, stop.

28:45.679 --> 28:47.148
That's enough.

28:48.083 --> 28:49.277
That's great.

28:49.628 --> 28:51.169
Thank you.

28:51.285 --> 28:53.163
Let me get that
last bone fragment.

28:53.249 --> 28:55.524
<font color="#ffff00">[Metal clinks]</font>

28:55.968 --> 28:58.802
All right, let's run
the potentials again, please?

28:59.161 --> 29:00.742
- <font color="#ffff00">[Computer Beeps]</font>
- See if she can walk.

29:00.827 --> 29:02.070
- <font color="#ffff00">[Computer Beeps]</font>
- Strong motor and sensory

29:02.155 --> 29:03.341
signals strength throughout.

29:03.426 --> 29:05.090
Okay, okay.

29:05.246 --> 29:06.520
As soon as we get out of here,

29:06.606 --> 29:08.942
we're gonna reposition her
for the C5 repair.

29:09.325 --> 29:12.325
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

29:13.415 --> 29:14.999
<font color="#00ff00">Alex:</font> Qadri, what do you see?

29:15.270 --> 29:17.153
Areas of necrosis.

29:17.262 --> 29:21.262
But I think we can find some
healthy islet cells in there.

29:22.740 --> 29:24.340
Kids are mean.

29:25.448 --> 29:26.664
I grew up in Utah.

29:26.749 --> 29:28.559
I was the
only non-Mormon in my school.

29:28.645 --> 29:30.903
They put a garter snake
in my backpack.

29:31.108 --> 29:32.606
I was fat.

29:32.955 --> 29:34.472
I was <i>me.</i>

29:34.557 --> 29:35.706
That would be hard.

29:35.791 --> 29:36.863
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

29:36.948 --> 29:39.552
Dr. Karev, nobody told me
you were starting.

29:39.637 --> 29:41.646
No one needed to.
You're not on this case.

29:41.731 --> 29:43.681
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

29:43.766 --> 29:45.989
I'm the reason she consented
to this surgery.

29:46.075 --> 29:47.770
After I told you to stay away
from her.

29:47.856 --> 29:49.028
I meant what I said, DeLuca.

29:49.114 --> 29:50.848
I don't want you anywhere
near this.

29:52.436 --> 29:53.891
I mean it. Get out.

29:53.976 --> 29:56.861
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

29:56.946 --> 29:58.296
<font color="#ffff00">[Door slides open]</font>

29:58.381 --> 30:00.298
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

30:00.383 --> 30:01.520
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

30:01.637 --> 30:03.718
- Can you get...
- This little bit right there?

30:04.787 --> 30:06.488
Thank you.

30:06.573 --> 30:07.872
I don't know how you do it.

30:07.957 --> 30:09.707
- Do what?
- Neuro.

30:09.889 --> 30:11.038
This much pressure?

30:11.124 --> 30:12.976
Brains and spines, life and death,

30:13.062 --> 30:14.785
every time you set foot
in an OR.

30:14.871 --> 30:16.137
I'd go crazy.

30:16.223 --> 30:19.090
Well, adrenaline's the only high
I let myself have anymore.

30:19.176 --> 30:20.668
I'm saying it's impressive.

30:21.847 --> 30:22.867
<font color="#ffff00">[Alarm beeping]</font>

30:22.952 --> 30:24.115
<font color="#00ff00">Neurophysiologist:</font> We're
losing the signal

30:24.200 --> 30:25.556
to both her
upper and lower extremities.

30:25.641 --> 30:26.707
What? Why?

30:26.793 --> 30:28.083
Did you Nick something
when we removed the disk?

30:28.168 --> 30:30.061
No, I wasn't anywhere near it.
Neither were you.

30:30.146 --> 30:31.785
Okay, why are we losing signal
like that?

30:31.871 --> 30:32.951
I-Is there residual disk? Penfield 4!

30:33.036 --> 30:34.426
Now they're gone completely.

30:34.512 --> 30:35.677
Is her blood pressure dropping off?

30:35.762 --> 30:36.739
Is she getting her fluids?

30:36.825 --> 30:37.868
Her blood pressure has been stable.

30:37.953 --> 30:39.937
This makes no sense.
Recheck the signal, please.

30:40.022 --> 30:42.121
Negative.
No response in arms or legs.

30:42.207 --> 30:43.285
All of it? It's all gone?

30:43.371 --> 30:44.931
Give her 1,200
milligrams of Solu-Medrol.

30:45.016 --> 30:46.739
- <font color="#00ff00">Nurse:</font> On it!
- She lost all of it?

30:47.160 --> 30:48.779
Arms and legs?
All of it?

30:48.864 --> 30:50.881
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

30:50.966 --> 30:52.397
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

30:52.482 --> 30:54.185
You look like
you're about to throw up.

30:54.270 --> 30:55.334
Oh, I'm not.

30:55.419 --> 30:56.567
<font color="#ffff00">[Groans]</font>

30:56.668 --> 30:58.224
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> You're
actually turning green.

30:58.309 --> 30:59.890
- You should get down.
- Nope.

31:00.637 --> 31:01.989
Gesture appreciated,

31:02.075 --> 31:03.676
but you don't have
to suffer with me...

31:03.762 --> 31:05.012
Yes, I do.

31:05.098 --> 31:07.101
I'm in this with you.
And her.

31:08.223 --> 31:09.809
We're in this together.
We're a family.

31:10.052 --> 31:11.848
Every step of the way,
okay?

31:12.871 --> 31:14.254
I know you're scared.

31:14.490 --> 31:15.746
I am, too.

31:15.958 --> 31:17.671
At least you know what to do.
You have Leo.

31:17.756 --> 31:18.809
<font color="#ffff00">[Scoffs]</font>

31:18.894 --> 31:20.918
Last night, I put
Leo's diaper on backwards,

31:21.004 --> 31:22.004
and he peed the bed.

31:22.090 --> 31:23.614
Poor guy had to sleep in wet sheets.

31:23.700 --> 31:26.550
Yeah. I mean,
we just do the best we can.

31:26.739 --> 31:27.989
It's all we can do.

31:28.328 --> 31:29.477
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

31:29.805 --> 31:31.551
<font color="#ffff00">[Breathes deeply]</font>

31:31.765 --> 31:32.807
Hey.

31:34.633 --> 31:37.809
Your mom... she's better than the best.

31:38.347 --> 31:41.265
She's incredibly
kind and hilarious,

31:41.350 --> 31:42.495
and she's so strong.

31:42.580 --> 31:45.731
I remember...
I saw her do a thoracotomy

31:45.817 --> 31:47.575
in a helicopter
that had no doors,

31:47.661 --> 31:49.434
and that patient lived,
yeah.

31:49.746 --> 31:51.035
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> Yeah.

31:51.454 --> 31:53.918
She listens to Duran
Duran <i>way</i> too loud...

31:54.004 --> 31:56.114
...and she can take down
an entire pizza on her own,

31:56.200 --> 31:57.573
which I find insanely
charming.

31:57.659 --> 31:58.942
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

31:59.028 --> 32:02.837
She is loyal,
and she is fierce, and...

32:04.106 --> 32:07.848
...she would lay upside-down
for weeks if you needed her to.

32:09.028 --> 32:10.427
You'll never turn around

32:10.513 --> 32:12.465
and not have her standing
right behind you,

32:12.726 --> 32:15.121
holding you up, okay?

32:16.410 --> 32:18.611
So, little one,
you do not have to worry.

32:20.189 --> 32:21.872
Your mom has got this.

32:21.957 --> 32:23.774
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

32:24.028 --> 32:25.176
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>
- Owen.

32:25.261 --> 32:26.492
<font color="#ffff00">[Knock on door, door opens]</font>

32:30.117 --> 32:31.681
Well, this is cozy.

32:31.767 --> 32:33.548
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>
- Hey, hi. <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> Hi, Tom.

32:33.633 --> 32:34.785
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font> Hey, Tom.

32:34.870 --> 32:37.133
- <font color="#ffff00">[Clears Throat]</font>
- God, is, uh, she okay?

32:37.219 --> 32:38.228
Are you okay?
How's the peanut?

32:38.313 --> 32:39.323
- She's fine. She's fine.
- Yeah?

32:39.408 --> 32:41.959
Just, apparently, I have cervix issues,

32:42.044 --> 32:43.994
and hopefully
not anymore after today.

32:44.281 --> 32:45.766
Thanks for the update, Hunt.

32:45.981 --> 32:47.578
Sorry,
I-I didn't want to worry

32:47.664 --> 32:49.066
any more people
than I needed to.

32:49.151 --> 32:51.035
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckling]</font> No,
I-I'm glad I'm here.

32:51.328 --> 32:53.172
Listen, I'll, um,
go get a coffee

32:53.258 --> 32:54.563
and check on a patient.
Do you need anything?

32:54.648 --> 32:55.906
No, good. We're good.

32:55.991 --> 32:57.074
- Hey, hey, give me one second, okay?
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door Opens]</font>

32:57.159 --> 32:58.337
Yeah.

32:59.461 --> 33:00.578
<font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

33:00.984 --> 33:02.012
So...

33:03.143 --> 33:04.703
I-I'm curious.

33:04.992 --> 33:06.884
Uh, if Teddy had been in actual labor,

33:07.125 --> 33:08.157
would you have told me then?

33:08.242 --> 33:10.342
Or would you still have let me
stay in that class?

33:10.427 --> 33:12.306
W... She wasn't in labor,
so what does it matter?

33:12.391 --> 33:14.742
Okay. Here we go.

33:16.078 --> 33:17.712
I know you don't like me.

33:17.797 --> 33:19.149
Trust me, I'm not losing
sleep over it,

33:19.234 --> 33:20.961
but if you plan to make
a play here?

33:21.070 --> 33:22.688
If you're gonna show up with a ring

33:22.828 --> 33:26.039
and take advantage of the very
old pain and vulnerability

33:26.125 --> 33:29.648
of a woman you have over and
over again hurt and abandoned...

33:29.734 --> 33:31.108
please rethink that.

33:31.492 --> 33:33.313
Because I will not lie down,

33:33.852 --> 33:35.883
and I will not walk away.

33:36.332 --> 33:37.836
I'll fight for her.

33:38.420 --> 33:40.750
And that'll bring on
a whole lot of drama and pain

33:40.836 --> 33:43.828
for the woman you claim
you just want to be happy.

33:44.084 --> 33:46.188
You don't know anything
about my history with Teddy.

33:46.289 --> 33:48.211
- Your history with Teddy...
- Yeah.

33:48.297 --> 33:49.693
...is you chose Amelia.

33:50.085 --> 33:50.994
More than once.

33:51.096 --> 33:53.406
My history is, I love Teddy.

33:54.977 --> 33:56.484
I mean, I'm in love with her.

33:57.019 --> 33:58.633
And only her.

33:59.429 --> 34:01.039
And she deserves to be with someone

34:01.125 --> 34:05.142
for whom she is
the first and the only choice.

34:05.227 --> 34:09.844
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

34:18.668 --> 34:20.657
Is she okay? Can I see her?

34:20.743 --> 34:21.945
<font color="#ffff00">[Ocie Elliott's "run to you" plays]</font>

34:22.030 --> 34:23.545
She's not awake yet, Toby.

34:23.630 --> 34:24.947
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

34:25.033 --> 34:26.783
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

34:27.043 --> 34:28.301
Your mom...

34:29.375 --> 34:32.136
suffered an injury
to her cervical spine.

34:33.190 --> 34:35.425
Her cord swelled in surgery.

34:36.011 --> 34:37.761
We did everything that
we could,

34:37.877 --> 34:41.777
but she is paralyzed
from the neck down.

34:41.862 --> 34:44.152
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ And I'll run ♪</font></i>
- Oh, my God.

34:44.237 --> 34:45.527
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ To you ♪</font></i>

34:45.612 --> 34:47.565
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ When the waters rise ♪</font></i>
- She's still here.

34:48.347 --> 34:50.472
- She's still your mom.
- <i>♪ And I'll run ♪</i>

34:50.596 --> 34:52.934
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ To you if the bombs ♪</font></i>
- She's gonna need a lot of help from you,

34:53.018 --> 34:55.339
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Ignite ♪</font></i> - from your family.
- <font color="#ffff00">[SNIFFLING]</font>

34:55.456 --> 34:58.433
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ I'll still call to you... ♪</font></i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Crying]</font> I can't. I'm not...

34:59.644 --> 35:01.950
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ ..if I lose my sight ♪</font></i>

35:02.036 --> 35:04.521
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ And I'll fall for you </font>♪</i>
- She's the one.

35:04.606 --> 35:06.992
- She's the one with the...
- All the answers.

35:07.120 --> 35:08.902
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

35:09.118 --> 35:10.652
Yeah, I have the same mom.

35:10.894 --> 35:12.027
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Hammering on ♪</font></i>

35:12.113 --> 35:15.034
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ a glass floor </font>♪</i>
- The smart, strong, fearless mom

35:15.120 --> 35:16.597
who always has more sense
than you.

35:16.683 --> 35:17.878
Yeah, I know it very well.

35:17.964 --> 35:20.863
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Rapping on a black door ♪</font></i>

35:21.034 --> 35:22.566
I have, um...

35:23.714 --> 35:26.480
- learned that it's now...
- <i>♪ Don't know what it's all for ♪</i>

35:26.566 --> 35:27.917
...now, when she's the one
that's hurt,

35:27.995 --> 35:29.691
when she's the one
that needs you...

35:30.910 --> 35:32.676
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Don't want it ♪</font></i>
- ..that's when you realize

35:32.761 --> 35:35.241
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Anymore ♪</font></i> - that she's already
given you all that you need.

35:35.437 --> 35:38.331
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ And I'll run to you ♪</font></i>

35:38.424 --> 35:39.779
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ when the waters rise ♪</font></i>
- You've got it. You're strong

35:39.864 --> 35:41.511
and fearless already.

35:42.142 --> 35:43.255
She already showed you how.

35:43.341 --> 35:44.764
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ And I'll run to you ♪</font></i>

35:44.850 --> 35:47.222
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ If the bombs ignite ♪</font></i>
- So...

35:48.599 --> 35:49.835
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ I'll still ♪</font></i>
- don't let her down.

35:49.920 --> 35:53.866
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Call to you if I lose my sight ♪</font></i>

35:53.991 --> 35:55.382
Can I be there?

35:55.468 --> 35:58.233
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ And I'll fall for you ♪</font></i>

35:58.319 --> 36:00.764
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ If you need a fight ♪</font></i>
- When she wakes up?

36:01.030 --> 36:04.428
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

36:04.866 --> 36:06.374
<font color="#00ff00">Jo:</font> <i>This is Jo. Leave a message!</i>

36:06.460 --> 36:08.148
- <font color="#ffff00">[Cellphone Beeps]</font>
- Hey, hey. I just, uh...

36:08.233 --> 36:09.953
I wanted to see
if you were still on the plane.

36:10.038 --> 36:12.452
I just... I can't wait
to hear how it went.

36:12.538 --> 36:13.850
<font color="#ffff00">[Cellphone clicks]</font>

36:13.936 --> 36:15.350
Look, I'm not some intern

36:15.436 --> 36:16.389
you can kick around anymore,
all right?

36:16.475 --> 36:17.711
What you did today
was unprofessional.

36:17.796 --> 36:19.772
No, what <i>you</i> did today
was unprofessional.

36:19.889 --> 36:21.155
The way you helped out Nora...

36:21.241 --> 36:22.617
that should have been
the first thing you did.

36:22.702 --> 36:24.625
But you're too pissed
at the world about your dad.

36:24.710 --> 36:26.976
And believe me, I know what a
number our parents can do on us.

36:27.061 --> 36:28.601
But you let it mess
with your job today.

36:28.686 --> 36:30.772
And with my patient's
really excellent mom.

36:30.858 --> 36:32.460
And it's messing with
your relationship.

36:32.546 --> 36:33.922
- My relationship?
- What does it have

36:34.007 --> 36:35.967
- to do with that?
- No, don't let it. Just don't.

36:36.097 --> 36:38.217
When people reach out a hand,
you don't bite it.

36:38.311 --> 36:39.538
I did it for years.

36:39.624 --> 36:42.061
The only thing it gets you
is they stop reaching out.

36:42.435 --> 36:47.923
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ And I'll be all for you
if you lose the fight ♪</font></i>

36:48.116 --> 36:49.592
Hey.

36:49.678 --> 36:51.289
- <font color="#ffff00">[Device Beeps]</font>
- What were your numbers this morning?

36:51.374 --> 36:52.586
Because if this is you
relaxing,

36:52.671 --> 36:54.389
I'm gonna have
to have you admitted.

36:54.483 --> 36:56.108
<font color="#ffff00">[Gasps]</font> Oh.

36:56.387 --> 36:59.421
Oh, well, maybe
there are outside factors.

36:59.507 --> 37:00.737
Huh?

37:00.874 --> 37:02.546
Just do it again.
Do it again.

37:02.824 --> 37:04.717
Is your, um, heart pounding?

37:04.803 --> 37:06.075
Your pulse racing?

37:06.444 --> 37:07.600
I'm not 13.

37:07.686 --> 37:10.577
Oho, oh. It never ends.

37:10.763 --> 37:13.031
<i><font color="#ffff00">[Muffled laughter]</font></i>

37:17.004 --> 37:18.676
- <i>Did you read that? That's huge!</i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

37:18.761 --> 37:20.890
- Hey.
- Hi.

37:21.582 --> 37:22.769
Everything is okay.

37:22.855 --> 37:23.899
Thank you.

37:23.985 --> 37:25.252
Yeah.

37:26.590 --> 37:28.281
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

37:29.217 --> 37:30.733
<font color="#ffff00">[Monitor beeping]</font>

37:30.818 --> 37:32.853
<font color="#ffff00">[Teddy laughing]</font>

37:34.021 --> 37:35.519
<font color="#00ff00">Meredith:</font> <i>If only life's variables</i>

37:35.605 --> 37:38.692
<i>were as cut and dried
as the rules of mathematics.</i>

37:40.700 --> 37:41.738
Hey.

37:41.824 --> 37:43.551
- Is this part of your study?
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

37:43.636 --> 37:46.090
Hm? Uh... Uh, yeah.

37:47.418 --> 37:48.589
This, too?

37:48.675 --> 37:50.464
Oh, no.
This... This is, um...

37:50.550 --> 37:52.293
This is
a little trigonometry

37:52.379 --> 37:53.996
mixed with a little calculus

37:54.082 --> 37:55.652
mixed with
a little logic.

37:55.738 --> 37:57.113
It is the stuff of
nightmares.

37:57.199 --> 37:58.316
It's...

37:58.402 --> 37:59.629
17.

37:59.807 --> 38:01.029
<font color="#ffff00">[Laughs]</font>

38:01.115 --> 38:02.298
Please.

38:02.383 --> 38:04.519
<i>If only there were clear answers.</i>

38:07.288 --> 38:08.616
17.

38:09.056 --> 38:10.940
<i>Certainty. Clarity.</i>

38:11.025 --> 38:12.310
<i>Right or wrong.</i>

38:12.396 --> 38:13.979
I want you to know...

38:14.804 --> 38:16.569
I will never,
ever forgive you for that.

38:16.655 --> 38:18.007
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

38:18.155 --> 38:19.382
I'm okay with that.

38:19.468 --> 38:21.959
<font color="#ffff00">[Benjamin Francis leftwich's
"when you were young" plays]</font>

38:22.069 --> 38:25.592
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

38:25.807 --> 38:27.657
<font color="#ffff00">[Knock on door, door opens]</font>

38:27.742 --> 38:32.686
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

38:36.483 --> 38:40.905
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ You sit there in your heartache ♪</font></i>

38:41.115 --> 38:44.841
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Waiting on some beautiful boy to ♪</font></i>

38:44.926 --> 38:49.145
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ To save you from your old ways ♪</font></i>

38:49.230 --> 38:50.713
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ You play forgiveness ♪</font></i>

38:50.798 --> 38:52.982
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Watch it now, here he come ♪</font></i>

38:53.209 --> 38:56.819
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ He doesn't look a thing like Jesus ♪</font></i>

38:56.904 --> 38:59.389
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ But he talks like a gentleman ♪</font></i>

38:59.474 --> 39:01.090
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Like you imagined... ♪</font></i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Lock Clicks]</font>

39:01.175 --> 39:05.621
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ ..when you were young ♪</font></i>

39:05.847 --> 39:09.051
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

39:09.660 --> 39:13.660
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ When you were young ♪</font></i>

39:13.988 --> 39:17.006
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

39:17.238 --> 39:19.108
<i>But all you can do is eliminate
as many</i>

39:19.193 --> 39:20.543
<i>- unknowns as possible..
- ♪ Can we climb this mountain? ♪</i>

39:20.628 --> 39:21.700
- Hey.
- Hi.

39:21.785 --> 39:23.106
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ I don't know ♪</font></i>

39:23.192 --> 39:26.230
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Higher now than ever before ♪</font></i>
- I'm talking first.

39:26.316 --> 39:28.285
- Okay.
- I'm talking first

39:28.371 --> 39:30.668
because
I don't do sitting at work

39:30.754 --> 39:32.777
wondering whether my boyfriend
is avoiding me...

39:32.863 --> 39:34.519
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>
- ..or being weird to me.

39:34.605 --> 39:37.676
It's just... I'm past
that point in my life.

39:38.152 --> 39:40.613
I'm not interested in it.
I have no time for it.

39:40.699 --> 39:42.699
I know.
I ran out of minutes.

39:42.785 --> 39:43.958
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ ...that started turning
when you were young ♪</font></i>

39:44.043 --> 39:45.134
What?

39:45.375 --> 39:47.191
The thing with my dad.

39:47.699 --> 39:49.566
I-I can't fix him, I can't help him,

39:49.652 --> 39:51.040
and I...

39:51.309 --> 39:53.309
couldn't believe
how much that hurt.

39:53.574 --> 39:55.058
And I needed
a minute to be hurt.

39:55.144 --> 39:57.146
I didn't want to drag you
down with me.

39:57.699 --> 39:59.916
I needed a minute, all right?

40:00.254 --> 40:01.254
But now...

40:01.340 --> 40:03.879
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Sometimes you close your eyes ♪</font></i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Sighs]</font>

40:03.965 --> 40:06.598
Now I just need you.

40:06.684 --> 40:07.918
<font color="#ffff00">[Sighs lightly]</font>

40:08.074 --> 40:10.527
Well, maybe I need a minute
now.

40:11.034 --> 40:14.262
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ When you were young ♪</font></i>
- Do you?

40:14.621 --> 40:16.496
- Do you really, though?
- Maybe.

40:16.582 --> 40:18.234
- I want to say yes.
- <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

40:18.410 --> 40:20.403
Maybe I do. <font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font>

40:20.691 --> 40:24.767
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

40:27.595 --> 40:32.486
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ When you were young ♪</font></i>

40:32.572 --> 40:33.989
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

40:34.097 --> 40:36.181
- Did you make that?
- Yeah.

40:36.267 --> 40:38.184
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ When you were young ♪</font></i>

40:38.526 --> 40:40.525
You cook and you speak Italian?

40:40.611 --> 40:42.642
<font color="#ffff00">[Chuckles]</font> You hungry?

40:42.728 --> 40:44.381
I'm starving.

40:45.045 --> 40:47.863
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ The devil's water,
it ain't so sweet ♪</font></i>

40:47.949 --> 40:50.322
Well, have a seat, and prepare
to have your mind blown.

40:50.408 --> 40:53.533
- Really? Wow, okay.
- Mm-hmm.

40:54.158 --> 40:57.767
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ But you can dip your feet in ♪</font>
- Then pick an answer and hope..</i>

40:58.775 --> 41:03.236
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Every once in a little while ♪</font></i>

41:03.408 --> 41:04.480
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

41:04.565 --> 41:05.781
Jo?

41:05.866 --> 41:07.850
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

41:08.074 --> 41:09.424
Jo, you asleep?

41:09.510 --> 41:14.635
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>

41:19.413 --> 41:23.322
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ You sit there in your heartache ♪</font></i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Whispering]</font> I missed you.

41:24.251 --> 41:27.469
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Waiting on some beautiful boy to ♪</font></i>

41:27.986 --> 41:31.874
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door Opens]</font>
- <i>♪ To save you from your old ways ♪</i>

41:31.959 --> 41:33.409
- <i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ You play forgiveness ♪</font></i>
- <font color="#ffff00">[Door closes]</font>

41:33.494 --> 41:36.312
<i><font color="#ff80ff">♪ Watch it now, here he comes ♪</font></i>

41:36.397 --> 41:38.214
<i>Hope that, at the end of the day,</i>

41:38.299 --> 41:40.158
<i>it's an answer you can live with.</i>

41:41.111 --> 41:45.955
<font color="#ff80ff">(♪♪)</font>
